Cash-strapped state oil company PetroSA has paid senior executives millions in bonuses despite a string of disastrous projects that resulted in a R14.5-billion loss the Sunday Times reported.It said eleven bosses received payouts totalling R17.3-million even after the board said they did not deserve themThe executives benefited from a legal opinion that said affordability would not qualify as a justifiable reason not to pay the bonuses.Furious mid-level employees this week accused their bosses of running a self-enrichment scheme and demanded repayment of the money. They said the bonuses were being paid while the company was laying off hundreds of staff to cut costs newspaper reported.